docs.summary:
Retrieves the events view information.
E.g. the current view end date, or the future duration in days the view should strive for.

members.name: externalId
members.doc: Optional conference ID in an external system.

members.name: guestUrl
members.doc: URL used by a guest to join the conference.

members.name: hostUrl
members.doc: URL used by the host to start the conference.

members.name: password
members.doc: Optional conference password.

members.name: type
members.doc: World known conference type, such as Zoom.

members.name: _id
members.doc:
Unique event ID.
Allows clients to ignore duplicate webhooks.

members.name: entityEventSequence
members.doc:
A sequence number defining the order of updates to the underlying entity.
For example, given that some entity was updated at 16:00 and than again at 16:01,
it is guaranteed that the sequence number of the second update is strictly higher than the first.
As the consumer, you can use this value to ensure that you handle messages in the correct order.
To do so, you will need to persist this number on your end, and compare the sequence number from the
message against the one you have stored. Given that the stored number is higher, you should ignore the message.

members.name: entityFqdn
members.doc:
Assumes actions are also always typed to an entity_type
Example: wix.stores.catalog.product, wix.bookings.session, wix.payments.transaction

members.name: entityId
members.doc: ID of the entity associated with the event.

members.name: eventTime
members.doc: Event timestamp.

members.name: originatedFrom
members.doc: If present, indicates the action that triggered the event.

members.name: slug
members.doc:
This is top level to ease client code dispatching of messages (switch on entity_fqdn+slug)
This is although the created/updated/deleted notion is duplication of the oneof types
Example: created/updated/deleted/started/completed/email_opened

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc:
Whether the event was triggered as a result of a privacy regulation application
(for example, GDPR).

members.name: deletedEntityAsJson
members.doc: Entity that was deleted

members.name: currentEntityAsJson
members.doc:
Since platformized APIs only expose PATCH and not PUT we can't assume that the fields sent from the client are the actual diff.
This means that to generate a list of changed fields (as opposed to sent fields) one needs to traverse both objects.
We don't want to impose this on all developers and so we leave this traversal to the notification recipients which need it.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Date the event was created.

members.name: _id
members.doc: The event ID.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date the event was last updated.

members.name: adjustedEnd
members.doc: Read-only end date adjusted to the Wix Business time zone, or `request.timeZone` if provided.

members.name: adjustedStart
members.doc: Read-only start date adjusted to the Wix Business time zone, or `request.timeZone` if provided.

members.name: appId
members.doc: ID of the Wix app owning the event, as derived from the schedule.

members.name: capacity
members.doc:
The event capacity, which is the max number of participants that can participate in the event.

The capacity is inherited from the schedule and can be overridden.

members.name: conference
members.doc:
Online conference.

The conference is inherited from the schedule and can be overridden.

members.name: end
members.doc: The event end date.

members.name: extendedFields
members.doc: Extensions enabling applications or users to save custom data related to the event.

members.name: inheritedFields
members.doc:
A list of fields for which values were inherited from the schedule or the recurring event,
if this event is an instance of recurring event.

members.name: location
members.doc:
The event location.

The location is inherited from the schedule and can be overridden.

members.name: notes
members.doc: Additional notes and information about the event.

members.name: participants
members.doc: The event participants.

members.name: permissions
members.doc:
List of granted permissions for this event.

Derived from the schedule and the resources of the the event.
Resources are granted with the `COMMENTER` role.

members.name: recurrence
members.doc:
Whether this event is a recurring event or an instance of recurring event.

The possible values are:
- `"NONE"` No recurrence, i.e the event is a single event instance. Default.
- `"MASTER"` The event is the recurrence master defining the recurrence rule, which is the repeat pattern for the events.
- `"INSTANCE"` The event is an instance of a recurring event. Read only.
- `"EXCEPTION"` The event is an exceptional instance of a recurring event. Read only.

members.name: recurrenceRule
members.doc:
The recurrence rule defining a repeating pattern for the event.
Required for `MASTER` recurrence, read only otherwise.

For example, a event that repeats every second week on a Monday until January 7, 2024 at 8 AM, will have the following recurrence:
- `frequency = WEEKLY`
- `interval = 2`
- `days = [MONDAY]`
- `until = 20240107T08:00:00Z`

members.name: recurringEventId
members.doc: The ID of the recurring event that this event belongs to, if this event is an instance of recurring event.

members.name: remainingCapacity
members.doc: The remaining number of participants that can be added to the event.

members.name: resources
members.doc:
List of resources affected by the event.

For example:
- Event occupying a resource time, such as a room, equipment or person.
- The Bookings App Staff is affected by the Booking Class Sessions it provides.

members.name: revision
members.doc:
The event revision number, which incremented on updates.

The current revision should be provided on updates to prevent conflicting changes.

members.name: scheduleExternalId
members.doc: The schedule external ID.

members.name: scheduleId
members.doc:
The ID of the schedule that the event belongs to.
Cannot change.

members.name: scheduleName
members.doc: The schedule name.

members.name: start
members.doc:
The event start date.

Recurring events must start from at least today.

members.name: status
members.doc:
The event status. Read only.

The possible values are:
- `"CONFIRMED"` Event is confirmed. Default value.
- `"CANCELLED"` Event has been cancelled.

members.name: timeZone
members.doc:
The event time zone, formatted according to the IANA time zone format.
Must be a regional time zone (Area/Location) or UTC.

The time zone is inherited from the schedule and can be overridden.

members.name: title
members.doc:
The event title.

The title is inherited from the schedule and can be overridden.

members.name: transparency
members.doc:
Specifies whether the event blocks the schedule time.
Default is true.

members.name: type
members.doc:
The event type.
Cannot change.

The possible values are:
- `"DEFAULT"` Default event.
- `"WORKING_HOURS"` The event represents a resource working hours. Working hours events are hidden by default from queries.

The Wix Bookings App, once installed, also provides the following:
- `"APPOINTMENT"` Bookings Appointment event.
- `"CLASS"` Bookings Class event.
- `"COURSE"` Bookings Course event.

See the [Event Type Provider](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/internal-only/calendar/event-type-provider-v3/introduction) for more details.

members.name: event
members.doc: The event which was added or updated within the view.

members.name: previousEvent
members.doc: Optionally, the previous event.

members.name: event
members.doc: The event which was removed from the view.

members.name: previousEvent
members.doc: Optionally, the previous event.

members.name: endDate
members.doc: The view end date.

members.name: futureDurationInDays
members.doc: The number of days the view lasts into the future.

members.name: extendedEndDate
members.doc: The extended events view end date.

members.name: appId
members.doc: ID of the Wix app owning the event

members.name: eventAddedOrUpdated
members.doc: Event has been added or updated within the view.

members.name: eventRemoved
members.doc: Event has been removed from the view.

members.name: eventAddedOrUpdated
members.doc: Event has been added or updated within the view.

members.name: eventRemoved
members.doc: Event has been removed from the view.

members.name: futureDurationInDays
members.doc:
The number of days the view lasts into the future.
Must be greater than the current value.

members.name: eventsView
members.doc: The updated events view.

members.name: namespaces
members.doc:
Extended field data. Each key corresponds to the namespace of the app that created the extended fields.
The value of each key is structured according to the schema defined when the extended fields were configured.

You can only access fields for which you have the appropriate permissions.

members.name: eventsView
members.doc: The events view.

members.name: wixUserId
members.doc: ID of a Wix user (site owner, contributor, etc.).

members.name: wixUserId
members.doc: ID of a Wix user (site owner, contributor, etc.).

members.name: _id
members.doc:
The location ID. Optional.
Currently only supported for locations of type `BUSINESS`, and used to reference the Wix Business Location.

members.name: address
members.doc:
The location address. Optional.
Derived from the Wix Business Location if the location is of type `BUSINESS`.

members.name: name
members.doc:
The location name. Optional.
Derived from the Wix Business Location if the location is of type `BUSINESS`.

members.name: type
members.doc:
The location type.
The possible values are:
- `"BUSINESS"` event takes place at the business location.
- `"CUSTOM"` event takes place at the custom location.

members.name: contactId
members.doc: The ID of the Wix contact.

members.name: email
members.doc: The participant email address.

members.name: name
members.doc: The participant name.

members.name: phone
members.doc: The participant phone.

members.name: list
members.doc: A full or partial list of the participants.

members.name: omitted
members.doc: Whether participants were omitted from the participants list.

members.name: status
members.doc:
The participants status.

The possible values are:
- `"CONFIRMED"` All participants are confirmed.
- `"PENDING_CONFIRMATION"` Some participants are pending confirmation..

members.name: total
members.doc: The total number of participants.

members.name: identity
members.doc: The identity granted the permission.

members.name: role
members.doc:
The permission role.

The possible values are:
- `"WRITER"` Role grants full write and read access.
- `"COMMENTER"` Role grants full read access and permission to edit notes.

members.name: adjustedUntil
members.doc: Read-only until date adjusted to the Wix Business time zone, or `request.timeZone` if provided.

members.name: days
members.doc:
The days of the week when the event should be repeated.
Currently, only a single day is supported.

members.name: frequency
members.doc: The frequency with which the event should be repeated.

members.name: interval
members.doc:
Works together with `frequency` to specify how often the event should be repeated. Default is `1`.
For example, `WEEKLY` frequency and `interval` of `2` means once every two weeks.

members.name: until
members.doc:
The date until which the event should be repeated.
When it is not specified, the event repeats forever.

members.name: _id
members.doc: The resource ID.

members.name: name
members.doc: The resource name.

members.name: transparency
members.doc:
Specifies whether the event blocks the resource time.
Default is true.

members.name: type
members.doc: The resource type.

members.name: localDate
members.doc:
Local date time, in ISO-8601 format.
E.g, "2024-01-30T13:30:00".

Note: seconds are not supported and ignored.

members.name: timeZone
members.doc: The event time zone.

members.name: utcDate
members.doc:
The UTC date determined by the server.
Not returned for adjusted dates.

description: A date time with a time zone, having the UTC offset and date determined by the server.
